comments: Barnes (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) at the end of the drive.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Bazley (OKC) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Siakam (TOR) reaches across Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and makes contact with his body to get to the ball, which affects Gilgeous-Alexander's SQBR on the transition play.
During the drive, Champagnie (TOR) moves alongside Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and marginal body contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander is able to maintain his intended path to the basket.
Siakam (TOR) jumps to the side of Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) on his contest and marginal follow-through contact occurs after the release of the driving shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) and Bazley (OKC) make incidental foot to foot contact as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
Siakam (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Siakam (TOR) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Dort (OKC).
Dort (OKC) places a resting hand to VanVleet's (TOR) front and marginal contact occurs simultaneous to VanVleet temporarily losing control of the ball during his dribble move.
Siakam (TOR) is slightly late to establish himself in Dort's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs with his side as he goes over the pick and maintains his defensive matchup.
Dort (OKC) legally contests VanVleet's (TOR) jump shot attempt to his side when incidental body contact occurs after VanVleet's release.
Barnes (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Giddey (OKC).
Dort (OKC) moves laterally into VanVleet's (TOR) path and makes contact with his body, which affects his SQBR on his drive.
Trent Jr. (TOR) extends his arm across and makes contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arms, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) is firming up in Dort's (OKC) path when marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Dort (OKC) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Champagnie's (TOR) leg, which does not affect his SQBR during his drive to the basket.
Giddey (OKC) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position as he absorbs the body contact during Champagnie's (TOR) shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) briefly grasps Siakam's (TOR) jersey as both players disengage, and the marginal contact does not affect Siakam's ability to get to the inbounds pass.
VanVleet (TOR) releases his inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) briefly places a resting hand on VanVleet's (TOR) shoulder, and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by VanVleet (TOR).
Bazley (OKC) cleanly blocks VanVleet's (TOR) driving shot attempt before making marginal contact with VanVleet's body after VanVleet has landed.
Replay Review overturns the call on the court as there is clear and conclusive evidence showing that the ball is still in Champagnie's (TOR) hand when the game clock expires.
